---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServicesGrid from '~/components/ServicesGrid.astro';
import CountiesGrid from '~/components/CountiesGrid.astro';
import ErrorCodesGrid from '~/components/ErrorCodesGrid.astro';
import FAQ from '~/components/FAQ.astro';
import CallCTA from '~/components/CallCTA.astro';
import { BUSINESS } from '~/data/business';

const title = `Samsung Refrigerator Repair | Same-Day Service | ${BUSINESS.phoneDisplay}`;
const description = `Same-day Samsung refrigerator repair across ${BUSINESS.areasServed.join(', ')}. Family Hub, Bespoke, French Door, side-by-side. Call ${BUSINESS.phoneDisplay}.`;

const homeFaqs = [
  {
    question: 'Do you offer same-day Samsung refrigerator repair?',
    answer:
      'Yes — most calls received before noon can be scheduled the same day across our five service counties. Booking is open 24/7 and our service hours are Mon–Sun 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which Samsung refrigerator models do you service?',
    answer:
      'All current Samsung refrigerator lines: Family Hub, Bespoke, French Door, 4-Door FlexZone, side-by-side, and top-freezer models. We also service older Samsung models still under common parts availability.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does a Samsung refrigerator repair cost?',
    answer:
      'A diagnostic visit covers travel, inspection, and a written quote. Repair pricing depends on the part — common ice-maker and sensor failures fall in a different range than compressor or sealed-system work. We always quote before any repair.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you fix Samsung ice makers?',
    answer:
      'Yes — Samsung ice makers (especially the French Door ice room) are one of the most common calls we run. We carry the most-failed parts in the truck.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What areas do you cover?',
    answer: `${BUSINESS.areasServed.join(', ')}. We do not currently serve outside these five counties.`,
  },
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} showHero={true}>
  <div style="max-width:600px; max-height:600px; margin:0 auto;">
    <img
      class="responsiveimg"
      alt="Professional Samsung Refrigerator Repair Services"
      src="/images/samsung-refrigerator-repair-services.webp"
      width="600"
      height="600"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="maintext">
    <h2>Samsung Refrigerator Specialists Since 2010</h2>
    <p>
      We're a mobile Samsung refrigerator repair service running same-day calls across five Southern
      California counties — Los Angeles, Orange, Riverside, San Bernardino, and Ventura. Samsung is
      our specialty, not a side line. Our trucks carry the parts that fail most on Samsung French
      Door, 4-Door FlexZone, Family Hub, Bespoke, side-by-side, and top-freezer models, so most
      repairs finish on the first visit.
    </p>
    <p>
      Samsung refrigerators have well-documented failure modes — the French Door ice maker freeze-up,
      the defrost-system fault that warms the fridge while the freezer stays cold, the inverter board
      that throws an 84C code and looks like a dead compressor. Knowing those patterns is the
      difference between a single-visit fix and a misdiagnosis. We've spent years working only on
      Samsung, and we won't replace a $400 main board when the actual failure is a $40 sensor.
    </p>
    <p>
      Booking is open 24/7. Service hours run Mon–Sun 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM. Calls received before noon
      generally get a same-day arrival window. Diagnostics include a written quote, and no work
      starts until you approve the price.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="maintext">
    <h2>When to Call a Samsung Refrigerator Technician</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Our team specializes in Samsung refrigerator repairs across {BUSINESS.areasServed.length} Southern California counties.</li>
      <li>Most repairs are completed on the first visit thanks to truck-stocked Samsung parts.</li>
      <li>We serve {BUSINESS.areasServed.join(', ')}.</li>
      <li>If you spot any of the issues below, stop using the unit and book a technician — DIY work on sealed systems voids most warranties.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div id="issues"></div>
  <div class="maintext">
    <h2>Common Samsung Refrigerator Issues</h2>
    <h3>1. Temperature Fluctuations</h3>
    <p>Inconsistent temperature in the fridge or freezer often points to a defrost-system fault, a failing evaporator fan, or a damper that has stuck closed.</p>
    <h3>2. Excessive Frost Buildup</h3>
    <p>Frost on the freezer wall or around food packaging usually means the defrost heater, defrost thermostat, or main control board is failing to run a complete defrost cycle.</p>
    <h3>3. Water Leakage</h3>
    <p>Water inside the produce drawers or on the floor in front of the unit usually traces to a clogged defrost drain or a cracked water inlet valve.</p>
    <h3>4. Unusual Noises</h3>
    <p>Buzzing, clicking, grinding, or knocking noises typically come from the compressor, condenser fan, evaporator fan, or ice maker auger.</p>
    <h3>5. Faulty Ice Maker</h3>
    <p>Samsung French Door ice makers are the single most-repaired Samsung component. Symptoms range from no ice to freeze-ups to leaks.</p>
    <h3>6. Display Panel Errors</h3>
    <p>Codes like 1E, 5E, 21E, 41C, 84C, OF OF, or PC ER indicate a specific subsystem fault. See our <a style="color:#fff; font-weight:700;" href="/error-codes/">error code guide</a> for what each one means.</p>
    <CallCTA />
  </div>

  <div id="repair"></div>
  <ServicesGrid heading="Samsung Refrigerator Repair Services" />

  <div id="maintenance"></div>
  <div class="maintext">
    <h2>Samsung Refrigerator Maintenance</h2>
    <p>Annual maintenance on a Samsung refrigerator means cleaning the condenser coil, verifying the defrost cycle, inspecting the door gaskets, and confirming temperature accuracy across both compartments.</p>
    <p>Twin Cooling and FlexZone systems benefit most — they have more sensors and more failure points than a basic top-freezer model. A 30-minute maintenance visit catches the small failures before they become a fridge full of warm food.</p>
    <CallCTA />
  </div>

  <ErrorCodesGrid heading="Samsung Refrigerator Error Codes" limit={6} />

  <CountiesGrid heading="Counties We Serve" />

  <FAQ faqs={homeFaqs} heading="Frequently Asked Questions" />
</Layout>
